==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subimago
<hw>Sub`i*ma"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Sub-</er>, and <er>Imago</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
stage in the development of certain insects, such as the May flies,
intermediate between the pupa and imago. In this stage, the insect is
able to fly, but subsequently sheds a skin before becoming mature.
Called also <altname>pseudimago</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

